The great ends of life can by no means be so easily or readily realised as Socialists imply in their schemas of social organisation. Labour is the law of life; hard labour is the sign of earnest life. In the sweat· of the brow the vast majority of men must est their breed. In the sweat of the brein the mental worker must hammer out his thoughts. In the bloody sweat of a broken heart the martyr must consummate his sacrifice.
